column8: P1. Invest in innovation and the development of environmentally-friendly practices and industries (e.g. eco-tourism, sustainable agriculture).
column9: P2. Reduce funding for extractive and resource-intensive industries.
column10: P3. No new coal mines, close all existing coal-fired power plants as soon as possible.
column11: P4. Strengthen environmental protection regulations, such as regulation around mining and agriculture, to better protect the reef.
column12: P5. Maintain current levels of environmental protection.
column13: P6. Reduce current environmental regulations to boost local business.
column14: P7. Maintain current mixture of industries, land uses and practices (e.g. mining, refineries, agriculture and tourism).
